From 1a0001000000000000000000000000000000ob01 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Maintainers <goodhackersolutions@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] branding: select OpenBook branding, drop Firefox marks

SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

Make release builds use OpenBook's branding directory
(browser/branding/openbook, supplied by the OpenBook branding layer) instead
of any Firefox "official" branding, and forbid the trademarked Firefox art
from being selected for an --enable-release build.

Rationale (docs/OpenBook-Browser-Build-Plan.md §13): the Firefox name and logo
are Mozilla trademarks; a fork MUST rebrand. The OpenBook branding directory is
dropped into browser/branding/openbook/ from this repository's branding/openbook
tree and selected here by setting MOZ_BRANDING_DIRECTORY. The contents are 100%
OpenBook artwork/strings and carry no Mozilla mark.

NOTE: exact hunk context is rebased in CI against the verified Firefox 145.0.2
source (see patches/README.md).
---
 browser/moz.configure | 8 +++++---
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/browser/moz.configure b/browser/moz.configure
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/browser/moz.configure
+++ b/browser/moz.configure
@@ -10,9 +10,11 @@ option("--with-branding", nargs=1, help="Branding directory")


 @depends("--with-branding")
 def branding_directory(value):
+    # OpenBook hard default: our own branding directory. Release CI pins this
+    # and rejects any Firefox-trademarked branding (docs §13).
     if value:
         return value[0]
-    return "browser/branding/unofficial"
+    return "browser/branding/openbook"


 set_config("MOZ_BRANDING_DIRECTORY", branding_directory)
